  <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 1, 1867, p. 
    779-780: "Cleanthes, a Stoic, born at Assos in Troas about B.C. 300...He first placed himself
    under Crates, and then under Zeno, whose faithful disciple he continued for 19 years....</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">
    Brill's New Pauly: "Cleanthes, 2, from Assus, stoic philosopher, C. of Assus. Stoic
    philosopher and second head of the school. Biographical information is derived from
    Diogenes Laertios (7,168-176) and Philodemus' History of Stoicism (Coll. 18-29)...." 
    Inwood, Brad (Toronto). "Cleanthes." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: 
    Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2009. Brill Online.
  </mads:note>  
